description.narrative: (Malawi): USAID/Malawi's Support for Service Delivery Integration-Systems activity will strengthen health sector policies, management, leadership, and fiscal responsibility. FY 2015 activities include:-Technical assistance to Ministry of Health (MOH) on implementation of health financing strategy, key policies, and guidelines that affect Essential Health Package delivery;-Logistical and operational support to the National Malaria Control Program;-Leadership and management coaching to central and district health managers and financial management coaching to district health management teams;-Technical assistance to customize the Human Resources Information System to the needs of the GOM so as to increase and improve use of this and District Health Information Systems data; and-Supporting the MOH in using a new mobile technology tool for Supportive Supervision in 15 districts.Activities will result in improved policies and increased capacity of MOH to deliver the Essential Health Package.
